A secure file encryption and decryption system built using Python and Flask, designed to protect files through encryption, authentication, and access control mechanisms. The project implements secure file handling using cryptographic techniques and includes additional security features such as OTP verification, activity logging, and brute-force protection.

🚀 Features

✅ File Encryption & Decryption using Fernet encryption
✅ Secure key generation using SHA-256 hashing
✅ OTP-based user authentication
✅ Login protection and session management
✅ Failed attempt tracking and brute-force prevention
✅ Activity logging for monitoring user actions
✅ Secure file upload and download workflows

🛠 Technologies Used
Python
Flask
Cryptography (Fernet)
SHA-256 Hashing
HTML/CSS
Session Management
File Handling
🧠 System Workflow
User logs in using credentials
OTP verification is performed for authentication
User uploads a file for encryption/decryption
Encryption key is generated using SHA-256
Files are encrypted/decrypted using Fernet symmetric encryption
System logs activities and tracks failed attempts for security
🔒 Security Features
OTP Authentication
Session-based access control
Brute-force attack prevention (failed attempt limiting)
Activity monitoring and logging
Password-based encryption key generation

Future Enhancements
Email-based OTP delivery
Multi-user authentication system
AES encryption support
Cloud file storage integration
Deployment using Docker / Cloud services
